<section class="attrs" aria-label="What Eleven is">
  <h2>Eleven is&hellip;</h2>

  <div class="attr">
    <h3>Effortless to join</h3>
    <div class="attr-body">
      <p>
        One link opens the whole app in any browser — no install, no account,
        no phone number. Grandparents included: nothing to set up, text as
        big as they need, and one click to save your chats for keeps.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="attr">
    <h3>Unreadable to anyone else</h3>
    <div class="attr-body">
      <p>
        Messages and photos are encrypted on your devices before they travel.
        If someone stole our servers tonight, they’d hold gibberish — no
        names, no messages, no photos. Not &ldquo;we promise not to
        look&rdquo;. <em>Can’t</em> look.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="attr">
    <h3>Yours</h3>
    <div class="attr-body">
      <p>
        No ads, no tracking, no algorithm deciding who sees what. Only the
        person who runs a space ever pays — and you can move the whole thing
        onto your own computer whenever you like. That’s the point.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p style="margin-top: 1.25rem">
    <a href="/features/#eleven-is">More &rarr;</a>
  </p>
</section>

